{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/emacsswiftmodule"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift library to write Emacs plugins in Swift!"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Getting started","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/DefiningAModule","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/CallingLispFunctions","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/DefiningLispFunctions","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/TypeConversions","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/ErrorHandling"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/Lifetimes","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/AsyncCallbacks"],"title":"Advanced"},{"title":"Environment","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/Environment","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/RuntimePointer"]},{"title":"Type conversions","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/TypeConversions","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/EmacsConvertible","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/OpaquelyEmacsConvertible","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/EmacsValue","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/PersistentEmacsValue","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/Symbol"]},{"title":"Error handling","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/ErrorHandling","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/EmacsError"]},{"title":"Asynchronous callbacks","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/AsyncCallbacks","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/Channel","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/Environment\/openChannel(name:)"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/Module"],"title":"Protocols"},{"title":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/ConsCell"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/EmacsVersion","doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/List"],"title":"Enumerations"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"module","title":"EmacsSwiftModule","modules":[{"name":"EmacsSwiftModule"}],"roleHeading":"Framework","externalID":"EmacsSwiftModule","role":"collection"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Emacs Swift module provides a convenient API for writing "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/www.gnu.org\/software\/emacs\/manual\/html_node\/elisp\/Writing-Dynamic-Modules.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" in Swift. It marries a dynamic nature of Emacs Lisp with strong static typization of Swift and hides the roughness of the original C API together with harder aspects of that language such as a lack of closures and manual memory management. It also translates Emacs Lisp errors and Swift exceptions into each other."}]},{"level":2,"text":"A Quick Tour","type":"heading","anchor":"A-Quick-Tour"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"EmacsSwiftModule","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" allows you to call functions from Emacs Lisp using Swift’s own types."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let two: Int = try env.funcall(\"+\", with: 1, 1)","assert(two == 2)","try env.funcall(\"message\", with: \"%S %S\", \"Hello\", 42)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And define your own Lisp functions out of Swift closures"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["try env.defun(\"foo\") {","  (x: Int, y: Int) in x + y","}","try env.defun(\"bar\") {","  (input: [String]) in input.joined(separator: \", \")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"that can be easily used in Emacs Lisp"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"emacs-lisp","code":["(foo 1 1) ;; => 2","(bar [\"Hello\" \"World\"]) ;; => \"Hello, World\""]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It handles errors on both sides so the user can almost always simply ignore them."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["try env.defun(\"always-throws\") { (x: Int) throws in","  throw MyError(x: x)","}","try env.defun(\"calls-afdsiufs\") {","  (env: Environment) in","  do {","    try env.funcall(\"afdsiufs\", with: 42)","  } catch EmacsError.signal {","    print(\"Whoops! It looks like 'afdsiufs' doesn't exist!\")","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And on the Lisp side too","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"emacs-lisp","code":["(always-throws 42) ;; => raises (swift-error \"Swift exception: MyError(x: 42)\")","(calls-afdsiufs) ;; => nil because we caught the error"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The same happens when a type requirement expected in Swift is not met."}]},{"code":["(foo \"Hello\" \"World\") ;; => raises (wrong-type-argument numberp \"Hello\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"emacs-lisp"}]}],"references":{"doc://EmacsSwiftModule/documentation/EmacsSwiftModule/AsyncCallbacks":{"abstract":[{"text":"Calling Lisp functions without an active Environment.","type":"text"}],"title":"Asynchronous Callbacks","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/EmacsSwiftModule\/documentation\/EmacsSwiftModule\/AsyncCallbacks","role":"article","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/emacsswiftmodule\/asynccallbacks"},"doc://EmacsSw